<p>President Vladimir Putin and Russia&#x27;s top general announced that Moscow tested the nuclear‑powered, nuclear‑weapon‑capable cruise missile known as the Burevestnik on October 21, with officials saying it flew about 14,000 km and remained airborne for roughly 15 hours . Russian leaders described the trial as successful and said they would move toward deploying the system, while characterizing it as having a near‑unlimited range and the ability to challenge existing defenses . The announcement came during a visit by Putin to an army command post amid Russia’s ongoing operations in Ukraine, linking the test to broader strategic planning . Independent verification was not supplied in the cited reports, which relay Russian statements and official briefings .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/K7YkrmZQ2N2HEHbPyoLYnIa3Afc-NzMpyHF7uWkmHMdqgxMYa6CJx-CrdlSNhieGVl4V9b16HijCUx5sclBedGJzqE9vfTvu0rUEoBMvYo24te6xemOQV3tKPvA-_SY28AFGBs6D0BRug3zO5Tt--tBgFkjTH_kEd7z7VB_KCQ' alt='Russian officials at a military briefing after announcing the Burevestnik test' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Operational claims: Russia&#x27;s chief of the general staff said the missile completed long, multi‑hour flight profiles and performed vertical and horizontal maneuvers, and that the observed flight distance did not represent the weapon&#x27;s technical limit</li><li>Detection limits: Russian accounts say the weapon is difficult for conventional radar to detect and can only be tracked by specialized spacecraft during launch and acceleration phases, complicating standard air‑defence monitoring</li><li>Strategic timing: Officials announced the test while Putin was briefed at an army command post on the line of contact with Ukraine and on strategic nuclear forces exercises, tying the test to military posture and planning</li><li>Program history: Moscow first disclosed the Burevestnik project in 2018 and has framed the system as a long‑range strategic capability since then</li></ul><blockquote>The technical characteristics of the Burevestnik missile make it capable of striking highly protected targets at any distance with guaranteed accuracy - Valery Gerasimov</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President Vladimir Putin: Putin presented the test as successful and said Russia would move toward deploying the weapon, describing it as a unique product in Moscow&#x27;s arsenal. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/russia-central-asia/article/3330366/putin-russias-new-nuclear-powered-missile-can-evade-any-defence'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>Chief of the General Staff Valery Gerasimov: Gerasimov briefed that the missile carried out a roughly 15‑hour flight with complex maneuvers and said the distance covered was not the system&#x27;s limit. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/russia-tested-new-nuclear-powered-cruise-missile-says-top-general/article70204310.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/russia-central-asia/article/3330366/putin-russias-new-nuclear-powered-missile-can-evade-any-defence'>Putin: Russia’s new nuclear-powered missile can evade any defence</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rt.com/russia/626971-nuclear-missile-test-russia-burevestnik/'>New unlimited-range cruise missile can bypass air defenses – Russian military</a> - rt.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/russia-tested-new-nuclear-powered-cruise-missile-says-top-general/article70204310.ece'>Russia tested new nuclear-powered cruise missile, says top General</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/putin-claims-russia-successfully-tested-new-nuclear-powered-cruise-missile/'>Putin claims Russia successfully tested new nuclear-powered cruise missile</a> - timesofisrael.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/russia-tested-new-nuclear-capable-missile-putin-top-126873456'>Russia has tested a new nuclear-capab